# example 5
sim39 <- grf(961, grid="reg", cov.pars=c(1, 0))
## grf: generating grid  31  *  31  with  961  points
## grf: process with  1  covariance structure(s)
## grf: nugget effect is: tausq= 0 
## grf: covariance model 1 is a pure nugget effect
## grf: decomposition algorithm used is:  cholesky 
## grf: End of simulation procedure. Number of realizations: 1
image(sim39)

## simulao com estrutura espacial isotropica
sim40 <- grf(961, grid="reg", cov.pars=c(1, .15))
## grf: generating grid  31  *  31  with  961  points
## grf: process with  1  covariance structure(s)
## grf: nugget effect is: tausq= 0 
## grf: covariance model 1 is: exponential(sigmasq=1, phi=0.15)
## grf: decomposition algorithm used is:  cholesky 
## grf: End of simulation procedure. Number of realizations: 1
image(sim40)

## simulao com estrutura espacial anisotropica
sim41 <- grf(961, grid="reg", cov.pars=c(1, .15), aniso.pars=c(pi/4, 3))
## grf: generating grid  31  *  31  with  961  points
## grf: transforming to the isotropic space 
## grf: process with  1  covariance structure(s)
## grf: nugget effect is: tausq= 0 
## grf: covariance model 1 is: exponential(sigmasq=1, phi=0.15)
## grf: decomposition algorithm used is:  cholesky 
## grf: back-transforming to the anisotropic space 
## grf: End of simulation procedure. Number of realizations: 1
image(sim41)

# example 6
sim51 <- grf(100, ylims=c(0,0), cov.pars=c(1, 0.25))
## simulations in 1D
## grf: simulation(s) on randomly chosen locations with  100  points
## grf: process with  1  covariance structure(s)
## grf: nugget effect is: tausq= 0 
## grf: covariance model 1 is: exponential(sigmasq=1, phi=0.25)
## grf: decomposition algorithm used is:  cholesky 
## grf: End of simulation procedure. Number of realizations: 1
sim51$data <- 10 - 5*sim51$coords[,1] + sim51$data
image(sim51, ty="l")

# example 7
sim61 <- grf(961, grid="reg", cov.pars=c(1, 0.25), lambda = 0)
## grf: generating grid  31  *  31  with  961  points
## grf: process with  1  covariance structure(s)
## grf: nugget effect is: tausq= 0 
## grf: covariance model 1 is: exponential(sigmasq=1, phi=0.25)
## grf: decomposition algorithm used is:  cholesky 
## grf: Data transformed (Box-Cox), for lambda = 0
## grf: End of simulation procedure. Number of realizations: 1
image(sim61)

hist(sim61$data)

# example 8
sim71 <- grf(121, grid="reg", cov.pars=c(1, 0.25))
## grf: generating grid  11  *  11  with  121  points
## grf: process with  1  covariance structure(s)
## grf: nugget effect is: tausq= 0 
## grf: covariance model 1 is: exponential(sigmasq=1, phi=0.25)
## grf: decomposition algorithm used is:  cholesky 
## grf: End of simulation procedure. Number of realizations: 1
sim71$data <- rpois(121, exp(0.5 + sim71$data))
image(sim71, col=gray(seq(1,0.2,l=11)))
text(sim71$coords[,1], sim71$coords[,2], sim71$data)

barplot(table(sim71$data))
